# Private, non-repo discussion notes (monetization, etc. — never committed)
/_private/

# The inspector's embedded SPA bundle (built by `make inspector-bundle` from
# web/inspector into internal/inspector/dist/ for the `//go:embed all:dist`
# directive in internal/inspector/assets_embed.go) is now COMMITTED, not
# gitignored (D-187). The earlier "never commit the build artifact" scheme
# (D-098, then the .gitkeep-only anchor) left every distributed binary —
# `go install …@latest` and the cross-compiled GitHub Release downloads alike —
# embedding only the placeholder page, because neither channel runs the local
# `make inspector-bundle` step. Committing the bundle is the only way
# `go install` (which builds from the module proxy's committed source) ships a
# working inspector. CI regenerates it and `git diff --exit-code`s the tree
# (`make inspector-bundle-check`) so the committed bundle can never drift from
# web/inspector source.

# VitePress docs site (Phase 29) — install + build artefacts. The site source
# is tracked under docs/site/ (.vitepress/config.ts, index.md, etc.); the
# node_modules tree and the built dist/cache are produced by `make docs` and
# never committed.
docs/site/node_modules/
docs/site/.vitepress/dist/
docs/site/.vitepress/cache/

# Playwright MCP scratch directory (locally captured screenshots are copied
# into docs/screenshots/phase-NN/ for the PR; the raw .playwright-mcp/
# directory is never committed).
/.playwright-mcp/
